Description:

Architecture / Interior Design office located in the NYC Flatiron District specializing in the design of contemporary high-end custom home interiors. We are currently seeking a professional candidate to work directly with principal who is passionate about contemporary interior design, self-motivated, capable of handling multiple projects efficiently with minimum supervision. Must be creative, innovative, highly detailed-oriented, and have excellent analytical and problem-solving skills.

Responsibilities:
• Perform leadership role designing projects in all phases of design, from programming to contract administration;
• Have a good understanding of interior finishes, materials, furniture, lighting, fixtures, and FF&E schedules and budgets for residential projects;
• Prepare presentation boards, AutoCAD drawings (including electrical & lighting plans), elevations, renderings, specifications, purchase orders and invoices;
• Manage the development of design from initial site measuring until final installations of FF&E;
• Visit job sites to address and resolve construction/installation issues;
• Schedule and conduct Client meetings to keep Clients current on proposed designs;
• Review submittals, shop drawings, substitutions and field conditions for conformance with design intent;
• Coordinate with outside team members such as contractors, vendors, workrooms and R&D companies;
• Track project tasks for multiple projects simultaneously; keep track of invoices, budget and timelines;
• Communicate with vendors, visit showrooms to select samples necessary for presentations.

Required Skills and Experience:
• 3-4 years post-graduate design experience with large experience working in high-end residential interiors projects;
• Bachelor's Degree in Interior Design or Architecture is a must. Master's Degree and/or NCIDQ are a plus;
• Proficiency in AutoCAD, REVIT, Photoshop and Sketchup;
• Excellent writing and communication skills;
• Excellent organizational and teamwork skills, with meticulous attention to detail;
• Must be proactive in anticipating Client questions;
• US Citizen or have a current work visa for work in the US

Salary: Competitive compensation commensurate with experience

